For the second time this month a Flybe plane was forced to make an emergency landing at a Belfast airport.

The plane carrying 69 passengers landed safety at Belfast City Airport after the pilot requested emergency landing procedures be deployed.

The Flybe flight from Southampton was approaching the airport when the crew was alerted by a smoke indication from the baggage hold, the airline said. 

