'The crew took the necessary action and the aircraft landed safely. 

Passengers evacuated the aircraft immediately by both front and rear stairs as normal and were bussed to the terminal.

'Flybe confirmed there was no sign of smoke in the aircraft after the landing but said that the incident would be 'fully investigated'.

The airline said the safety of its passengers and crew was its 'number one priority' and added that it 'regrets any inconvenience experienced'.

Earlier this month, a Flybe flight from Glasgow to Belfast made an emergency landing due to an engine fire.That incident is also under investigation. 

